  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to the Minimal profile and carries a content hash but no digital signature, leaving structural integrity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven achieved levels fall below required levels, six are flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. Decision outcome recorded as Accepted for adversarial-sample testing purposes.",
